23/08/2006
DAMASCUS, Syria -- Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul said on Tuesday (22 August) that Syria welcomed Turkey's efforts to resolve the crisis in the Middle East and would back Turkey's potential participation in a future UN peacekeeping force in Lebanon. His remarks followed talks in Damascus with Syrian counterpart Waled al-Muallem, President Bashar al-Assad and other senior officials. Gul also said the discussions were very positive and useful. He voiced the hope that, despite the Lebanon crisis, there is a chance for peace in the Middle East. (Sabah, NTV - 23/08/06)
